name: H5N2 avian influenza
summary: A man in Mexico has become the first person to die from the H5N2 strain of bird flu. The World Health Organization (WHO) confirmed the death and said there were no cases of human-to-human transmission. The H5N2 strain is a type of avian influenza that affects birds, but it can also infect humans. The virus is spread through contact with infected birds or their bodily fluids. Symptoms of bird flu in humans include fever, cough, sore throat, and muscle aches. In severe cases, the virus can cause pneumonia and respiratory failure. The H5N2 strain is not as common as other strains of bird flu, such as H5N1 and H7N9. However, it can be more deadly. The WHO is monitoring the situation and working with health authorities in Mexico to investigate the case and prevent further spread of the virus.

name: Echidna
summary: In an extraordinary and unprecedented event, a tiger shark was observed regurgitating an intact echidna, a spiny anteater native to Australia. This astonishing incident, witnessed by scientists during a three-year tagging project, has left them baffled and amazed. The regurgitated echidna was found in the shark's stomach, and its presence has raised questions about the feeding habits and capabilities of these marine predators.
